What is true about the differences between copyleft and permissive open source licenses?
Select the best answer.

A.
Copyleft licenses require derivative works to be released under the same license, while permissive licenses allow derivative works to be released under any license, though they may require changes to be documented.
B.
Copyleft licenses are used for software, permissive licenses for hardware
C.
Copyleft licenses are only for personal use, while permissive licenses are for commercial use  
D.
Copyleft licenses are the opposite of copyright licenses and allow free usage/distribution, whereas permissive licenses require permission to use/distribute
